The paper deals with video analysis and action localization, which are primarily computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel architecture that involves mining and attention mechanisms, which are common in machine learning and deep learning research. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves designing effective modules and exploiting contextual information, which are related to artificial intelligence and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible sub-categories.
